My neighborhood is nearby to the college that I attend, and for that I quite enjoy living there. There are mostly apartment buildings, but a few restaurants and bars that are fun to go to and aren't terribly expensive to go to. One of the bars was just renamed, and that one is more expensive to go to but it isn't really the worst quality of service or drinks there. Most of the people are nice. They are either college kids or they are lower income, since the apartment housing isn't very expensive. There's a lot of children nearby since there is an elementary school within walking distance of my apartment. I don’t know my neighbors, but I don’t really want to. They smoke a lot of weed and so the management of my building put an air freshener unit right across from their door, which my boyfriend and I found very funny. It’s almost insulting. The buildings that are around me are usually pretty old looking but might have renovated interiors. Down the street a bit there are brand new apartments, but I don’t like them because I know the construction done on them wasn’t particularly good. They’re cheaply built but the rent is expensive, which I think is such a scam but because they’re near campus, the management of those buildings can get away with it. There is a really cheap restaurant about five minutes from where I live that serves food only on paper plates and most of what they make is microwaved. Then across from that is a gas station, which I’ve heard isn’t a very good place to work. But thanks to some money from the city, the road was redone last summer so that there’s a nice big sidewalk, lots of grass on the medians and sides of the roads, and now the area is a little nicer. But the apartment building I live in is shrouded in tress. They cut a few of them down, so there are a few stumps, but there are a lot more trees where I live than down the road. Behind my apartment complex is a tree line and then another set of apartments. I live on 42nd street, but right behind is 43rd street and that one isn’t as nice. The sidewalks are really bad and falling apart, and most of the buildings on it look shabby. There are a lot of trees on this street, but that is probably to hide what the buildings look like. Most of the crime in my area has happened at an apartment complex on that street, but then again, I can’t blame just them. There are apartments across the street from me that also have a lot of crime and a rather transient population. But I think I like where I live. I can afford it, and there’s plenty of useful amenities nearby. I especially like how the university is within walking distance and there are two bus stops so that I can get to the store and downtown with ease.
My neighborhood is made up of duplex's on a cul-de-sac. They are intermittently placed and spaced so that they look like individual houses. The only difference is each is painted yellow with white porches and green metal roofs. Almost everyone, but not all, are friends with each other. We stand at the end of a not pre-decided driveway some evenings and chit chat while the small children of the neighborhood play with their toys, sidewalk chalk or fly their kites. It is very refreshing in this modern all to mechanical/computer filled world. It is rather like stepping back in time. We are surrounded by fields and trees enhanced by blue skies and white billowing clouds. The only downfall? This season, we are experiencing tornado warnings and for the first time, last night we actually heard actual tornado sirens so we had to head towards shelter. Sure enough, you would have found me in my bathtub clutching my littlest dog along with my purse and a few pillows. My big dog wanted nothing to do with the bathroom and remained in the livingroom, nervous and barking, nervous about the odd circumstances. The neighborhood was quiet except for the sound of large hail which fell all bout the ground. After the storm the road literally was steaming from the change of temperature. We went from 92 to 75 in a matter of minutes. The hail immediately melted when it hit the hot pavement. As I looked up towards the clearing skies, the sun came out and it started to rain. A double rainbow apparated. I ran into the house and grabbed my camera. Quickly snapped pictures to share with my Facebook friends and family. They were in awe, as was I. The streets remained quiet for another hour, before some people finally came home from wherever they were when the thunderstorm hit. Then it was business as usual, mom’s and children outside as dinner cooked. Such a friendly neighborhood for this gal who has recently moved form NH to NC. I adore the southern accent that people speak with. I have a two bedroom and two bath apartment, as does everyone. Though all the houses look the same on the outside, not all of the apartments are the same on the inside. Some are actually quite tiny. It doesn’t make sense to me. I love to walk along the biggest field behind where I live and mosey down to the pond that is not made for swimming. I have seen deer and in the morning you can hear the giant bullfrog singing his song. It is a fantastic place to live just forty minutes outside the city of Charlotte. Each morning is welcomed by the sound of roosters crowing from the surrounding farms. It is rather like living in a small community village of it’s own. We even have a donkey at a nearby farm that you can hear braying in the evening to let us know he is there. I was lucky to find this gem of a neighborhood.
I moved to this neighborhood just when I was about to start eighth grade. It was hard for me to make friends at first, but I ended up getting close to someone who lives two houses down from me and another guy that lives on my street. Neither of them lives there anymore but the memories are still there. The same people who lived here when I first moved here are still here for the most part. My neighborhood is pretty similar to your average American suburban neighborhood. The neighborhood has a lot of two-story houses in it. Every weekend or just whenever it is warm outside I hear the kids playing outside. The neighborhood is quiet most days of the week. I have never had a problem with any of the people in the neighborhood. You are left alone in this neighborhood unless you need help. I have ordered multiple packages online and have never gotten a package snatched off of my porch. I feel like I can trust my neighbors. There is a park a minute or two away from my house. I have a lot of memories there. I have played basketball, football, and baseball there with the other guys in the neighborhood before. I also ended up with one of my worst memories there when I got elbowed in the nose playing football, but the good memories outweigh the bad. Nowadays, whenever I go to that park it is to spend time with my cousin's kids. They are much younger than me and still like playing on swings and slides and all of that type of stuff. Just the thought of going to the park makes them excited. The park makes me very nostalgic for a number of different reasons now. The neighborhood is very diverse. You will find all kinds of food nearby. In just a one mile radius, you would be able to find Chinese, Indian, Mexican, and Italian restaurants. However, nowadays, a lot of people just use apps just as GrubHub and DoorDash to get their food delivered to them. The most popular food places are the fast food shops but you can get those near pretty much any suburban neighborhood. There are also plenty of pizza places. The stores here contain everything you would ever need. There are multiple dry cleaners nearby. There is a Walgreens and a CVS on the same street as well as a Jewel-Osco grocery store, which is popular in the Midwest. Some of the stores are even diverse as there is an Indian-owned store if you are ever in the mood to make some homemade Indian food or to buy some ready-made Indian food. Overall, I am a fan of my neighborhood. Reading on social media and seeing on the news some of the horror stories other people have to go through with their neighbors makes me grateful for mine.
My neighborhood is a quaint little town. It doesn't stand out from any other in South Carolina, but it's got a significant impact on the agriculture sector. Johnston is known as the Peach Capital of the World, something that the town proudly boasts about on the welcoming sign. It's primarily composed of farmland dominated by either peach trees or cattle. Houses that aren't located within the main part of town are widely spaced apart; most are two stories with either metal roofs to help combat the blazing summer heat or gray shingles. More often than not these houses aren't located near the road, but are further back allowing for the front fields to be used for animals/crops. Within the main part of town, there's a single stop light that hangs at a four way. Here is where the only stores in the entire town are located. There are three places in which you can get "fast food': Hong Kong, a small Chinese restaurant run by a single family, Fiesta Mexican Restaurant, or Gary's, a small burger chain. There used to be a pizzeria, however it closed down a short time ago. There is a very small family-owned pharmacy called Maxwell and Halford Drug; funnily enough, they're best known for the Cherry Coca-Cola they sell. There is a small, but expensive grocery store called Independent Grocers Alliance, more commonly known as IGA. While it is the only grocery store in the entire town, many individuals only stop to pick up one or two items; most prefer to travel to a Walmart in Batesburg-Leesville in order to purchase the majority of their groceries. The most popular store in the entire town is Dollar General; this store sells a vast array of everyday items and it often busy from the moment it opens until closing time! There is a very small furniture store, Possibilities Furniture & More, run by a kind woman who is well-known within the community. The store has been in Johnston for a plethora of years and even employs two movers who will deliver the purchased furniture! Attached to the furniture store building is a small pet groomers called Clark's Cuts and Kennels. They provide a multitude of services such as daycare, boarding, grooming, nail grinding, bathing, etc. Both a doctor's and veterinary practice are situated away from the primary part of town; they are both very small practices, though well-equipped to aid the residents of Johnston. There is a single elementary school called Johnston Elementary School. Once students have completed fifth grade, they must attend both middle and high school in the next town over. There are technically no parks within the town, however they are currently in the midst of creating a 2.5 acre recreational area in order to provide families with more opportunities to enjoy outings and attract more visitors/potential residents. Admittedly there isn't much to do; there are no movie theaters, bowling alleys, "hang out" spots, playgrounds for children, areas to walk pets, or a large variety of restaurants. Despite this it's a nice town, so small that you could pass in the blink of an eye without realizing!
The first time I'd heard of my place, I was listening to a podcast about people who'd gone missing. It was a little surprising. Almost every apartment in the area was going for over a thousand dollars a month. I'd never heard anything about that story and neither had any of my friends. Maybe it's the struggle. I know a few of my friends cry themselves to sleep at night. Things are expensive, but we've learned how to be frugal over the years. You start to like the dusty smell of flea market toys and mothballed clothes. You smell a lot less in adulthood. You might start to smoke, or you might just be too accustomed to the state of things. But the flea market always asserts itself. The smell of adulthood is dusty magazines stacked on a closed piano. It wedges itself in the leather and stays in even after you wash it. Here, there're 3 thrift stores in walking distance. If you start on the far side, you can patronize two charity thrifts, a library, a rare book store, and a curio shop. Downtown is dense, cars and people fill the streets every morning, but you'd never hear it in the thrifts. No matter how many people or cars pass by, the store is silent. It's a nice place to lose an afternoon. Every year, there's more and more of those. Cars and people flood it. It's a developing city, they say. Headquartering one of the largest online empires for e-commerce and delivery, it's still showing growing pains. It reminds me of New York. Everything and everyone is set on their own goals, and there isn't a whole lot anyone asks from you. You can be alone, quiet, and independent, and people will leave you alone. It's not like the South, where being a little concerned means you care. You don't pry into anyone's life here, really. You can keep up your shell as long as you'd like, and the city will crash and roll back like waves on the beach. It's a lively place to be. Between the pianist next door and the two amateur vocalists upstairs, there's always something going on. In a way, we have less of an apartment of strangers and more a community of friends. We come together for our needs, celebrate birthdays, mourn funerals, and help each other when we can. In a way, I'm lucky to be here. I quite like most of my neighbors and they treat me pretty well. I try to make sure to clean after myself and leave them food and they do the same in kind. I bring mail to them and they to me. It's nice to see them and I believe they enjoy my presence as much as I do theirs. I live in a massive, dehumanizing modernist sprawl but it's people like my neighbors that make me feel like I didn't totally ruin my life.
The general area in which I live in can be described as your typical cookie cutter suburbia. For my neighborhood in particular, the presence of a homeowner's association is very apparent. Upon entering, you'll see nothing but well-maintained single family homes, which we can thank the homeowner's association for. The front yards are all very similar. There's a small patch of landscaped grass, some decorative pebbles, and rather short driveways. Every so often you'll see small trees as well. Everyone has a two car garage. As you continue to drive along throughout the neighborhood you'll see newly paved concrete. Despite many different families living here, the roads are in excellent condition. You won't find any potholes or anything like that here. Most of the houses are single story, but sometimes you'll see two stories as well. We don't have a typical mailbox set-up that you would expect for single family homes. There are no individual mailboxes in front of each house. Instead, it's more like apartments where there are a large grouping of mailboxes at the end of the street. Everyone uses a key to gain access their specific mailbox. And there's two larger lockers for packages. Again, you can thank the HOA and their obsession with uniformity for this. The location of my house is on the extreme edge of the nearby city, so my neighborhood can be described as part rural, part suburbs. As a result, we have a lot of land for, well, everything. There's multiple community pools to which anyone living here can access. It's well maintained and gated. And then there are various walking trails where you can walk your dog, or just go for an evening stroll by yourself. You don't have to visit a park to get your exercise in. The neighborhood is large enough that you can simply run around it and get more than enough exercise. Most of the community is made up of retired people. It's a very safe area, and everyone looks out for one another. Mixed in with that, we have a small amount of middle aged and young professionals too. In regards to the city, it's surprisingly large - at least by population - but also has a small time town feel. We have the vast majority of amenities that you come to expect and rely on. For example, we have a exactly one mall. It's not huge, but it gets the job done. For me, it takes around 15 minutes of driving to get anywhere significant, but once I do that, I am greeted with many different stores to choose from. We have everything from high end grocery stores where you can get organic food, to bargain outlets that only stock a small selection of items and has bare minimum staff to keep costs down. All in all, my neighborhood is safe, well-maintained, and pretty typical. We have a lot of nice things, like pools and walking trails. And although we aren't right next door to any sort of shopping, you can just hop in a car and go to any major chain that you'd like.
I live in a small Midwestern town that is just outside the suburban areas of a major city. My immediate neighborhood, on the east side of the town, could be described as the most economically disadvantaged area of the town. Property values are low, with most houses being rented to or owned by low-income individuals. However, it is not unattractive or unpleasant. My neighbors are generally friendly people who will smile and say hello when I walk down the street. Crime rates, while slightly higher than other parts of town, are still generally low. There have been a few violent crimes in the past ten years within a few blocks of my home, including a few shootings and at least one homicide. Our next door neighbors lost their son in a shooting outside an area bar last year. Fortunately, our family has not been directly affected by crime other than having an occasional item disappear from our porch if we forget to bring it inside. In general, the town in which I live has been profoundly affected by the “opioid epidemic” that has affected many parts of the United States. Many lives have been lost due to fentanyl overdoses. Fortunately, there are many resources in my town to combat this epidemic, including several addiction rehabilitation centers and Narcan training sessions for families and friends of those affected by addiction. Despite these challenges, this town has many positive attributes. My son’s elementary school has excellent staff, from the principal to the teachers and support staff. Despite having special needs, he has not faced any bullying thus far due to the incredibly positive atmosphere of the school, and he loves it there. We have an active PTO that plans multiple events throughout the year to promote family involvement and educational progress. Because over 20% of our town’s population lives below the poverty level, the elementary school provides free breakfast and lunch to all students, so that no child ever has to go hungry. No child or family is treated as “less than” due to an inability to pay, and costs for school fees, supplies, and field trips are very reasonable. The City Council and staff have made many improvements to the appearance of our town, including repaving roads, landscaping, and refurbishing city parks. Unfortunately, most of these improvements have taken place in the center of town and on the west side, where all of the shopping areas are located and most of the traffic passes through. The east side where I live tends to be neglected, which is a point of contention for those in my neighborhood. Overall, I do enjoy living in this town. People are generally friendly, the schools are great, there are enough shopping options (both small businesses and larger retail stores) to meet my family’s needs, and our home may not be worth much, but it is comfortable and adequate. Our family has lived here for over 16 years, and we cannot imagine living anywhere else.
My neighborhood is full of culture. It's set upon a hill, surrounded by buildings with historical meaning. I live in a 7 story apartment building right across from the old live Theater, and a block down The Hill, is this cool little arcade bar that different types of people flock to on warm summer nights. Often times, especially on the weekends in June and July, you will see a line of people waiting to get in. A few blocks up is the nearest city park. It's pretty big considering the part of town it sits in. Encircling the park is concrete, with tall stairs poured into the wall. During the frigid winter months, homeless people set their tents up in neat little rows along the sidewalk and along the wide steps. It doesn't snow much, but it rains, and the torrential down pour in the mid-winter months often tends to make it difficult to keep warm. Setting their tents up close together, in the center of town rather than out in the jungle, keeps them much warmer. They're also within reasonable walking and transit distance to the only family center for miles, where they can bathe and shower. What I love about my city though, isn't the beauty of the historic nature- the tall proud buildings, the architecture that is spattered through-out the varying levels of the hills that roll down towards the ocean. What I love about my neighborhood is the culture of the people themselves. You see, Hilltop once was the most notorious neighborhood on the West Coast for gang violence. You still hear stories, even three decades later, about the federal government officials and the DEA sweeping through like a broom, trying to clean the streets. The people, they don't forget. Stories are still passed from generation to generation, on through to transplants like me, of those days. The people work hard, even though it's still considered one of the rougher 'hoods' in the entire city, to keep it cleaned up. They still care about what goes on in their city, on their block. They say that if you're white, you shouldn't walk around the Hill after dark. Truly, I believe that this warning is reminiscent of the old days, and it is tinged with the sour taste of social conditioning. Perhaps it is that I am just dark enough to pass for a not entirely "white-girl," or maybe Hilltop recognizes me as one of their own, someone who is just as painfully aware of the reminders that constantly plague our nation. Reminders that racism, cultural conditioning, and assumptions are made out of ignorance and fear, even in a city that is supposed to be a cultural melting pot Utopia. I know one thing: no matter how far I roam, the Hilltop is home. I feel alive walking those streets at night, meeting people who have more quickly and rarely nefariously offered me a jacket than to rob me. It's a place where laundromat owners have stayed open just a few minutes later so I could charge my phone when I had no where to escape from the rain. It's a place where I have sat, believe myself to be invisible, huddled against concrete store fronts on the most grey dreary of nights, only to have someone stop and look me in the eye, hand me a $5, and tell me I'm beautiful and valuable.
I live in Rural America, specifically small town Michigan. Where you go from farmland to small tourist cities. There is no big city malls, no Wal-mart, Target, or even an Applebee’s. Anywhere you need to go, you have to drive to get to. Despite that I live in one of the most beautiful places in the world surrounded by water. My “city” is surrounded by water. Beautiful Lake Michigan to one side, and Lake Charlevoix on the other. Everywhere you go you can find a beach to dip your toes in. My neighborhood, reflects the idea of small town. Houses are not stacked upon one another. They aren’t cookie cutter houses that are built the same. They are older homes, some of them being updated and remodeled some of them being older. Most homes have basements. Full Basements that you can see from the road. Many houses in the neighborhood have older aluminum siding. We have houses every color you can imagine in the blocks that surround my house. Most of the houses have yards. Yards with trampolines, and playsets. Some people have gardens, and fences for their animals. The houses resemble Middle America. Hard working people who work to make a living and are either raising families or have raised families. On any given day you will see kids running up and down the streets. You will also see people walking dogs, biking and rollerblading. Neighbors know neighbors and you can recognize who fits in and who doesn’t belong. You will see someone grilling outside and wave, or even someone that is walking their dog from a few blocks down and smile pleasantly. The lawns are kept in decent condition. Nobody has leaves piled up from fall time. Green grass is kept mowed and under control. If people have plants and bushes in their yards they are kept trimmed down. It isn’t a beautiful neighborhood that you drive into and think wow look at the nice homes, but one you drive into and think you can tell this would be a good place to raise a family. It’s quiet, peaceful and, and safe. While only average looking, it is exceptional for the fact that it represents what people want in the world, which is a safe place to land at the end of the day. Within walking distance there is the county sheriff’s department and jail. The Health department is just next to that. The city recycling center sits just down the road, and neighbors and residents from around the city utilize the services they provide. We have baseball and softball fields nearby where you can hear the announcers keeping score and calling the names of players. Our small town airport is next to that. You can be playing outside, or even inside and hear the rumbles of small engine planes taking off and landing. You can walk to get ice cream from the local ice cream place, and if you are really into it you can make it downtown from our neighborhood of homes. My kids can ride their bikes to the park which is only 8 blocks or so away. It is a really great place to live.
transformed_texts: I live in a large city. My neighborhood is very different. Different kinds of buildings are near each other - homes and businesses. Some businesses are offices. Others are stores, restaurants, and places to have fun. There are many new restaurants to eat at and stores to buy things in. Some stores are big and well-known. Others are small and new. They are in malls and on streets. These streets are close to quiet neighborhoods. There are also parks near my home. People take their young children to these parks. My neighborhood has many different kinds of people. We have a community for people who like same-sex relationships. We also have a community for Orthodox Jews and people who came from the Soviet Union. There are many people from different countries and cultures in our city. We have areas called Korea town, China town, and Little Armenia. They are a few miles from my home. But driving a few miles can take a long time because of traffic. Many people in my city do not walk. They like to drive. Our city is very busy and has bad traffic. It is hard to find a place to park. Many new buildings are being built in our city. This is because many people are moving here. Some people are unhappy about this. They do not want more people and cars. There are many kinds of homes in our city. Some people live in big apartment buildings. Others live in houses or smaller apartment buildings. Some homes are for one family. Others are for two families. My neighborhood is also different. People of many ages live here. I do not know most of my neighbors. We are not a close community like we used to be. When I was a child, I played with my neighbors. We were all friends.

My neighborhood is interesting. It has many houses. Most are for one family. Some houses are split into two, but still connected. My house has a small yard in front and a small driveway on one side. It looks like many houses in America from a long time ago. That was the American dream. Many people wanted to live in a place like this. But now, the dream is not the same. Many people are not as happy as they used to be. The yards are not as nice. But families still live here. Children play. There is a school here. It has been here for almost 90 years. It makes children think about their future. It makes older people remember the past. There are a few churches, but they are not full. People like to play basketball. All the houses look different, but feel the same. There is a big store called Super A. It is owned by an Arab family. They are the only Arab family in the neighborhood. Most people are African American. The streets are wide. Children play football. They stop when cars come by. Many people have lived here for a long time. They know their neighbors. There was a school for karate. But when people stopped watching karate movies, children stopped wanting to study karate. Now it is a store that sells medicine. There is a small movie theater. It shows old movies. People like to go there because it is cheap. The youth do not like it, but older people do. There is a highway near my town. We do not have an exit for the highway. People wanted to make an exit, but the older people did not want it. They said it would hurt the town. So, the city said no. We are building a new high school. We are trying to choose a symbol for our town. I think a robot with a country accent and a cabin would be a good symbol.

You might not notice it at first. It is behind a shopping center, not a place people usually think of living. But if you look closely, you will see a community. Behind the old shopping center and some hotels, you will find people living in small buildings called apartments. These buildings are next to each other like dolls in a row. Some of these buildings have problems, so we will not talk about them. The other buildings are different. Across the street is a college for students. It is quiet and sleepy. Students walk in at 7 in the morning with coffee. The gates creak open and close slowly. Commuters honk their horns and get upset when they have to wait. The road divides into two streets. One side has a park. There is a place to fix broken bones next to the park. The building has a nice porch and a fan that blows air. Children play in the park. They run and play on the grass. Old people walk their dogs and watch the teenagers on skateboards. They talk to each other about boys and TV shows. There is a restaurant with cheap food. There is a store to buy things for swimming. There is a place to get your nails done. You can fill your pool and get a manicure at the same time. There is also a place to buy frozen yogurt. Young people eat frozen yogurt and do tricks on their skateboards. This neighborhood is like a piece of America. It is a part of history that does not change much.

We were driving through many fields of corn. My friend asked, "Where is everything?" I said, "This is it!" I knew she would be surprised by the open space. She was from a city where a store was near her house. She had never seen so much open land.

I told her about growing up in a small town in Ohio. I shared with her what life was like. She was surprised to learn about my home. We were on a country road. We passed a big hole in the ground filled with water. The next place was my home. The houses were made of brick and a hard, rough material called stucco. Each house had a big piece of land that people liked to take care of.

In the spring, flowers were everywhere. The trees changed colors with the seasons. People had nice cars. They were shiny and clean after a good wash. As we continued down the road, I saw a friendly neighbor. He was always outside cutting his grass and singing. Everyone liked to laugh at him, but he was a kind person. He was a doctor a long time ago. Now he is older and not as funny. 

My house was next. There were geese in the side yard. They ran from a dog. In the back, there was a small stream. You could hear frogs and cows from the farms nearby. Across a bridge made of wood was a special place. The trees, herbs, and flowers grew there naturally. I spent much of my childhood in this place. I built forts and played with friends. In the winter, the yard was empty and the trees were bare. But it was beautiful. The snow made a winter wonderland. My sister and I would make snowmen and angels. We had a lot of fun.

We would fight as kids, but in the winter, we made snowballs and built shelters. We were happy and did not worry about anything. We were just kids.

Portland, Oregon is a special city. The city's unofficial slogan is "Keep Portland Weird". This means Portland is different from other places. Some people think this slogan reminds us of the past. The past Portland was less known and less expensive. It had many creative and unique groups of people. Now, many people from California are moving to Portland. They are building new homes. But Portland is still weird.

Weird means accepting of things that are not normal. But it does not mean Portland does not have modern things. We buy things from other countries, like China. Portland has many ways of being weird. Some people like yoga and some like business. We all like to have fun. My neighborhood is colorful. There are flowers, herbs, and vegetables in every yard. In the summer, we have free boxes. Free boxes are things people are giving away. They can be clothes, books, or other things. You never know what you might find.

Walking through the neighborhood is fun. Portland is full of people who like different things. Some people go to yoga with goats, and some go to soccer games. Portland has people who chase their dreams. Some people like to spend time at the bar. Unfortunately, Portland has problems. We have a problem with drugs. This is often caused by mental health problems. The cloud and rain in Portland do not help. We also have a homelessness problem. Our services are good, but not enough. The community is divided. Some people care for the homeless, but some people are angry.

The mountains are always there. They see the sun every morning and evening. I forget about them many times. But they are always there. They do not change. They do not get angry or sad. They are strong and steady.

When I am very stressed, the mountains remind me to look at them. When I see them, I feel better. They give me the strength to keep going. I can rest my worried mind and keep moving forward.

I moved here when I started college. The mountains near the campus are beautiful. They are the first thing that caught my attention. The university has many nice buildings and trees. But the mountains are special. They are the most beautiful things here.

The town is also very nice. There are many cafes where I studied for many hours. The town has a mix of old and new things. The old buildings are very beautiful. I can walk or take the bus to the main street. The street is busy and fun. But I can also escape to a quiet place near the library.

The town has two different feelings. It is busy and quiet at the same time. This makes it very interesting. I have many happy memories here. I remember walking with my friends in the park. I also remember running to the movie theater.

But the town also has sad memories. Everyone has sad times in life. I cried by the pond many times. I thought about my life and my future. I saw the turtles and ducks living their lives. I wondered about my own life. But then I looked up and saw the mountains. They are strong and steady. They reminded me to keep going.

I walked to the main street. The sun was shining. The mountains were in front of me. They were beautiful. They told me to keep moving forward. They reminded me to be strong.

Bensonhurst is a neighborhood in Brooklyn, New York City. You can easily find it. The public transportation system is very good. Many people use it. Bensonhurst is a busy area. You will see many Asian stores. This is because many Asians live here. Over the past 20 years, many Asians moved to Bensonhurst. Now, you see an Asian store on every block. These stores sell food and do laundry. People like these stores. They have good food at low prices. It is also very easy to buy things. I live near here. There are four Asian stores within two minutes of each other. This is very convenient.

Bensonhurst is not just for Asians. Many immigrants and their families live here. Some businesses are owned by Asians, but there are others too. There is a park near here. It has basketball courts, a big field for sports, and a playground for children. People of all kinds visit the park and play together. Bensonhurst has many small homes and co-op buildings. Most people live in two-family houses. The people here are generally nice, but can be noisy. They often drive quickly and play loud music. If you visit at night, be careful. This neighborhood is generally safe, but some people may cause trouble. I personally had a problem here in the past, but it was a long time ago. There are also people who steal packages. In New York City, people must clean up after their dogs. But here, many people do not follow the rules. You will see dog waste on the sidewalk every morning. Be careful and keep your shoes clean.

I live in a place where there are few sidewalks. Everything slopes downhill and my house is at the top of the steepest hill in my neighborhood. People call it the "work out hill" because many runners like to exercise there. Since there are no sidewalks on my street, people walk on the road. The road is bumpy in some places and can be hard to drive on.

Some of the wires on the street are old and broken. It rains a lot here and branches break the wires. The workers fix them, but the repairs look messy. There are many tall trees around my home. But many people don't like the trees. They want to cut them down because they block the view of the ocean. That's why the houses are built high on the hill. They have big windows to see the bay.

It is beautiful when the sun sets. The water shines and the sky turns orange. But it is often cloudy, so we see the sun through a mist. Most days are cloudy and damp. Moss grows on everything: cars, houses, and fences. I once left my car outside for a month and it was covered in moss. It took three hours to clean it off.

There are not many children in my neighborhood. The school is close, but most people are older and retired. Many people have dogs. They are often in people's yards or running down the street. If you leave a door open, they might come in. I once found a dog in my living room and had to chase it out.

Rabbits run around the area. They are big and the gardeners don't like them because they dig up the plants. But my cats like them and have chased most of them away. We also see small birds and hummingbirds. Sometimes a hawk or eagle flies by, but the crows chase it away.

There are no stores near my home, but if you walk downhill to the waterfront, there are restaurants that serve fresh seafood. The beach is not big, but the rocks by the water are fun to throw into the ocean. The bay is not very wide, and you can see the other shoreline even when it is misty.

I live in a small town in Tennessee. My street is between two main roads, so there is more traffic. But it is a quiet neighborhood. We know most of our neighbors. They work in their yards and homes every day. In the winter, we sled on a nearby hill.

I live in a house at the corner of our street. We see everyone who comes and goes. We know their cars. When we see a strange car, we notice it. Some people walk for exercise or to walk their dogs. Children ride their bikes. We are usually at home because we work from home. There are four of us: my wife, two daughters, and me.

We go outside and play. We even play in the rain. Sometimes we cook outside on our back deck. It smells good. We hear lawn mowers almost every day from March to October. Our neighborhood has many trees, so it is cool and there are leaves in the fall. We rake and burn the leaves every year. I like the smell of burning leaves.

We have not had much winter lately. It feels like a long fall. Our garage is at the back of our house. I like to work on my truck in the garage. When the garage doors are open, I feel connected to the neighborhood.

On holidays, our neighborhood is quiet. But on Thanksgiving and other holidays, we see our neighbors with their families. Cars park on the street. I like living here. If our street were not a main road, it would be perfect.

My neighborhood is in the middle of the desert. It is a dry and hot place. There is dirt everywhere. If you live here, you see brown all the time. When you see a green lawn, you know the person is working hard to take care of it. 

I lived here in the 1990s. Houses were far apart. Now there are more houses. But it still looks like a small town. Many places are changing in the same way. 

The people in my neighborhood are friendly. But some areas are not so good. I have old friends around me, and I like this neighborhood. We have big stores, like Food for Less and Smart. But we do not have many small, special stores. 

If you want to buy something special, you have to drive far. We do not have stores like Whole Foods. 

Most people work in construction. The city is not fully developed, so there is a lot of space to build. This worries me. I like things the way they are now. I left a big city and do not want to go back. 

I work in the construction field. I install drywall and T-bars. 

I like living here because of the animals. People come to the desert for its beauty. The desert is hard to live in, but it is home to many types of animals. We should respect the animals and the environment. 

I have three children. They like lizards and desert bugs. They are outside right now trying to catch them. 

We have some fun things to do in our town. Victorville is a good place for families. We have a big event called the San Bernardino County Fair. It is fun. You should visit us and see the snow in Wrightwood and take a winter sports lesson. If you like learning about the desert, go to the Victor Valley Museum. It has many cool things to see.

My neighborhood is different from others. I do not live in a normal neighborhood. I live on a college campus. My home is a dormitory. My community is the people who live with me in the dormitory and the people on the campus.

My neighborhood has homes, people, stores and a park. But it is not like other neighborhoods. My neighborhood has apartments, houses and dormitory buildings. 

There are three kinds of homes. One kind is an apartment. In an apartment, 2-4 people live in a room. There are 4-6 rooms on each floor. Each building has 2 floors. It can have 20 people.

Another kind is a house. These houses are for people who go to the school. They are 2-4 rooms. Some alumni live in these houses.

The third kind is a dormitory. Many students live in a dormitory. Each room has 2 people. Some rooms have only one person.

People from many cultures and ages live in my neighborhood. The staff lives in houses. New students live in dormitories. Older students live in apartments.

My neighborhood has many stores. You can buy food, clothes and other things. My neighborhood also has a park. It is a safe place for everyone. The park is clean and has no crime.

I have lived in this neighborhood for 10 years. I was sad when I first moved here from Riverdale. I missed my old home and my friends. But my mom and dad wanted the best for me and my sister. They wanted us to live in a better place. It had a good school and nice houses.

Over time, I made new friends and some new enemies at school. I got to know my neighbors a little. Mr. Glen and his kids are nice people. They are like a family to me. I like them very much. They got married, and I went to their wedding. It was fun.

Mr. Glen's wife, Ms. Veda, threw away her leg bandage. I caught it! I also like to hang out with their daughter Marsharii. I hope she is doing well. The neighborhood is like a maze. I have a GPS now, so I can explore it more. I have been with my friends Kason and Curtis. We like to play video games and have fun together.

I also like to go to the park. It is peaceful and calm. I bring sticks and practice my balance. I also bring my wooden sword and practice fighting. I have fun doing what I love. The neighborhood has a basketball and tennis court. I used to play tennis with my dad and Mr. Graves. They made us work hard, but it was fun.

I have had many happy times in this neighborhood. I have many stories. But these are the ones that I remember best. I think the best is yet to come.

My home is near the college where I go to school. I like living here. There are many apartment buildings. Some restaurants and bars are here too. They are not very expensive. One bar is new. It is more expensive, but the service and drinks are good.

Most people here are students or they have low incomes. They live here because the apartments are not expensive. There are many children here too. There is a school near my home.

I do not know my neighbors. They smoke a lot of marijuana. The management put a special machine near their door to make the air smell good. My boyfriend and I think this is funny.

The buildings around me are old, but the inside is new. Down the street, there are new apartments. But they are not good quality. They are cheap, but the rent is expensive. I do not like this.

Near my home, there is a restaurant. They serve food on paper plates. Most of their food is cooked in a microwave. Across from the restaurant is a gas station. It is not a good place to work. But the city fixed the road near my home. Now it is nicer.

My apartment building has many trees. Some of the trees were cut down. But there are still many trees here. Behind my building, there are trees and another apartment complex. I live on 42nd Street. Behind it is 43rd Street. This street is not as nice. The sidewalk is broken and the buildings are old. There are many trees on this street. This is to hide how bad the buildings look.

There is crime in my area. It happens at an apartment complex on 43rd Street. But I do not blame just them. There is crime at another apartment complex across from me too. But I like where I live. I can afford it. There are many useful things near my home. I like that the college is near and there are two buses to take me to the store and downtown.

My neighborhood has many houses on a street that ends in a circle. The houses look like separate homes. They are all painted yellow with white porches and green roofs. Most people are friendly, but not all. We stand on our driveways at night and talk to each other. We see children playing with toys, drawing with chalk, or flying kites. This is nice in a world with many machines. It feels like the past. We live near fields, trees, and blue skies with white clouds. However, we have a problem. This season, we have had tornado warnings. One night, there was a tornado. We went to a safe place. I was in my bathtub with my small dog and some pillows. My big dog stayed in the living room and barked nervously. The neighborhood was quiet, except for loud hail. The hail fell to the ground. When the storm ended, the road was hot. It was 92 degrees outside, but quickly became 75 degrees. The hail melted on the hot ground. The sun came out, and it started to rain. I saw a double rainbow in the sky. I ran inside and took pictures. My friends and family were amazed, just like me. The neighborhood was quiet for a while. Then, people came home from where they were when the storm started. It was business as usual. People were cooking dinner, and children were playing. I love living here. I moved here from a place in New Hampshire to North Carolina. I like the way people talk in the South. My apartment is nice, but not all apartments are the same. Some are small. I like to walk in the big field behind my house. I also like to visit the pond. I have seen deer and heard a big bullfrog singing in the morning. It is a great place to live, 40 minutes from the city of Charlotte. Each morning, I hear roosters crowing from the farms. It feels like I am living in a small village. We even have a donkey that brays in the evening. I am lucky to live here.

I moved to this neighborhood when I was going into eighth grade. It was hard for me to make friends at first. But I became friends with someone who lives two houses down from me and another boy who lives on my street. They are not my friends anymore, but I still remember them. The people who lived here when I moved here are still here. My neighborhood is like many other neighborhoods in America. There are many houses with two floors. I hear children playing outside on nice days. The neighborhood is quiet most days. I have never had a problem with anyone in the neighborhood. You can leave your packages outside and they will be safe. I trust my neighbors. There is a park very close to my house. I have many happy memories there. I played basketball and football with the other kids in the neighborhood. But I also hurt my nose playing football. Now I go to the park with my cousin's young children. They like playing on swings and slides. The park makes me happy and sad at the same time. My neighborhood is different. You can find many kinds of food near my house. There are Chinese, Indian, Mexican, and Italian restaurants within a short walk. Many people order food online and have it delivered to their homes. There are also many fast food places and pizza shops. There are stores with everything you need. You can find dry cleaners and a place to buy medicine. There is a grocery store and other shops. One store is owned by an Indian family. I like my neighborhood. Reading about problems with neighbors on social media makes me happy to have good neighbors.

My neighborhood is a small town. It is in South Carolina. This town is famous for peaches. It is called Johnston. Johnston is known as the Peach Capital of the World. This is written on a sign at the town's entrance.

The town has a lot of farmland. Most of the land is used for peach trees or cattle. Houses are not very close to each other. They are mostly two stories high. Some have metal roofs to keep people cool in the summer. Others have gray shingles.

People who live outside the town center have their houses far from the road. They use the front fields for animals and crops. In the town center, there is a traffic light that helps cars move safely. This is where you can find the town's stores.

There are three places to eat quickly. One is a Chinese restaurant called Hong Kong. Another is a Mexican restaurant called Fiesta. The third is a burger place called Gary's. There used to be a pizza place, but it closed. The town has a small pharmacy called Maxwell and Halford Drug. They are famous for selling Cherry Coca-Cola.

There is a small grocery store called IGA. This store sells food and other things. But many people go to a big store called Walmart in a nearby town to buy most of their food. The most popular store in Johnston is Dollar General. It sells many everyday things and is very busy.

The town has a furniture store called Possibilities Furniture & More. It is run by a kind woman. She has been there for a long time. She also has people who will help move the furniture. Next to the furniture store is a place to groom pets called Clark's Cuts and Kennels.

There are two small doctor's offices and a veterinary clinic outside the town center. They help the people who live in Johnston. The town has a small school called Johnston Elementary School. When the students are older, they go to school in the next town. The town is small and does not have many parks. But they are making a new park now. This will give families a place to go and visit.

The town is not very big. There are no movie theaters, bowling alleys, or places to walk pets. But it is a nice town. You can drive by it quickly without noticing it is there.

I first heard about my home on a podcast. It was about people who disappeared. The news surprised me. It said that many apartments cost over one thousand dollars a month. I did not know anything about this story. My friends did not either. Life is hard here. Some of my friends cry at night because they are very poor. But we have learned to save money. We like old things. We like the smell of old toys and old clothes. As we grow up, we smell less. We might smoke or get used to our situation. The city has a lot of old things. We have flea markets and thrift stores. There are three thrift stores near my home. If you start on one side, you can visit two stores that sell used things, a library, a store with old books, and a store with strange things. The streets are very crowded, but the thrift stores are quiet. It is a good place to spend an afternoon. Each year, the city gets more crowded. Many cars and people go there. It is a growing city. They say it is like New York. Everyone is busy and does not ask for help. You can be alone if you want. People will leave you alone. This is different from the South. In the South, if you care about someone, you want to know what is wrong. Here, people do not ask questions. You can be yourself for a long time. The city is lively. There is always music coming from the house next door or the people upstairs who sing. We are like a community. We help each other when we need it. We celebrate birthdays and help each other when someone is sad. I am lucky to live here. My neighbors are nice. We help each other. We share food and mail. It is nice to see them. I think they like me too. I live in a big apartment complex, but my neighbors make me feel happy.

I live in a common kind of neighborhood. It has many houses that look the same. The homeowner's association takes care of the area. The houses are well-maintained. They all have a small garden in front. There are also some decorative stones and short driveways. Some houses have two cars. The roads are in good shape. You will not see any big holes on the road.

Most houses have one floor. Some have two floors. We do not have a mailbox in front of each house. We have a big group of mailboxes at the end of the street. Everyone uses a key to get their mail. There are also two big boxes for packages.

My house is near the edge of the city. It is a mix of country and suburb. We have a lot of land. There are many community pools. They are well-maintained and locked. We also have walking trails. You can walk your dog or go for a walk alone. The neighborhood is big. You can run around and get some exercise. Most people who live here are old. The area is safe. Everyone helps each other.

Some people are middle-aged or young professionals. The city is big, but it feels like a small town. We have many things you need. For example, we have a big store called a mall. It is not very big, but it has everything you need. I can drive to any store in about 15 minutes. There are many stores with good food, cheap stores, and more.

My neighborhood is safe and nice. We have many good things like pools and walking trails. We are not close to many stores, but we can drive to them easily.

I live in a small town in the Midwest. It is near a big city, but not in the suburbs. My neighborhood is on the east side of the town. It is one of the poorer areas. Houses here are not very valuable. People who live here usually rent or own these houses. They are low-income people. 

My neighborhood is not ugly. People here are friendly. They say hello when I walk by. Crime rates are a little higher here than in other parts of the town. But they are still low. There have been a few violent crimes near my home in the past ten years. These crimes include shootings and one person was killed. Our neighbors lost their son in a shooting near a bar. Luckily, we have not been affected by crime, except for sometimes items disappearing from our porch.

The town I live in has a big problem. It is called the "opioid epidemic." Many people in the US have this problem. It is a big issue in our town. Many people have died from overdoses. We have many resources to help people with addiction. These resources include centers for people to get help and training for families and friends of people with addiction.

Despite the problems, our town has many good things. My son's school is excellent. The teachers and staff are very good. My son has special needs, but he is happy at school. He is treated well and does not get bullied. Our school has many events to help families and students. They give free food to all students. This way, no child has to go hungry. The town council and staff have fixed many roads and parks in our town. They also planted nice gardens. But most of these changes are in the center of town and the west side. This is where the shopping areas are. My neighborhood, on the east side, is still a little neglected.

I like living in this town. People are friendly. The schools are great. There are many stores to buy things we need. Our home is not very valuable, but it is comfortable. We have lived here for over 16 years. We do not want to move.

My neighborhood is full of culture. It is on a hill. Many old buildings are around me. I live in a 7-story apartment building near an old theater. Across from the theater is a small bar with games. People like to go there on warm nights. There is a long line of people waiting to get in.

A few blocks away is a big city park. It is near my neighborhood. The park is surrounded by concrete. There are many stairs in the wall. In cold winter months, some people without homes set up tents on the sidewalk and the stairs. It is hard to stay warm in the rain. But they stay close together in the center of town. They are near a place where they can wash and take a shower.

I like my neighborhood. I do not like the old buildings and the hills. I like the people. Many years ago, my neighborhood was a bad place. There was much crime. The government and police came to clean up the streets. But the people remember. They still tell stories about those times. The people work hard to keep their neighborhood clean. They care about their city.

Some people say I should not walk around at night. They say it is not safe. But I think this is old thinking. Maybe people think I am like them. I am also aware of the problems in the world. We have problems with racism and not understanding each other. But my neighborhood is different. People are kind to me. They offer me their jackets when I am cold. They help me when I need it. They tell me I am beautiful and valuable. This is why I love my neighborhood.

I live in a small town in Michigan, America. This town is different from big cities. We do not have big shopping centers like Wal-mart or Target. We do not have big restaurants like Applebee's. If we need something, we must drive to get it. But our town is very beautiful. We are surrounded by water. We have a big lake called Lake Michigan to one side. We also have another big lake called Lake Charlevoix to the other side. We can find a beach to swim in everywhere we go. My neighborhood is like a small town. The houses are not close together. They are not the same. Some houses are old and some are new. Many houses have basements. People can see the basements from the street. Most houses have aluminum siding. The houses in my neighborhood are every color you can think of. Many houses have yards with trampolines and play equipment. Some people have gardens and fences for their animals. The people in my town work hard to make a living. They are raising families or have raised families. On any day, you can see children playing in the streets. You can also see people walking dogs, riding bikes, or rollerblading. Neighbors know neighbors. We can tell who is new and who is not. We wave and smile at each other. The lawns are kept clean. We do not leave leaves on the ground in the fall. The grass is cut and looked after. People take care of their plants and bushes. Our neighborhood is not perfect. It is a good place to live because it is quiet and safe. We have a sheriff's department and a health department near us. We also have a place to recycle and a park where people can play baseball and softball. We have a small airport near the park. We can hear the planes taking off and landing. We can walk to get ice cream and other things we need. My children can ride their bikes to the park, which is eight blocks away. It is a great place to live.
